Steps to Processing the Company Inbox

**Assess whatâ€™s coming in**

* ## Is it for a pending case? 

  ## If so, forward the email to the appropriate person (owner of that product board), then drag it to the appropriate sublabel on the left

* ## Is it carrier marketing communication?

  ##  If so, determine wealth or health, then drag it to the carrier communications sublabel under Medicare or  Retirement

* ## Is it commission related?

If so, review the commission sublabels under Commission and drag it to the appropriate label

* ## Is it regarding one of our agents licenses, appointments, or ce credits?

If so, drag it to the appropriate sublabel under L\&A

* ## Is it a notification from a carrier on an existing policy?

Review client contact to see if there is an open opportunity that aligns with the reason for the email, if not open an opportunity on the proactive service board for our team to work. Attached the email and/or any documents in the email

**Label Clean Up**

* How often should this be cleaned up?

The label folders should be cleaned up every 180 days, items older than that should be deleted 

* How to clean up

After determining what date the cut off is for the 180 days, group select all items older than that and move to trash, repeat process for every folder 

# Communication Guide\!

# **RPI Service Team Communication Processes & Scripts**

## **Core Philosophy Change**

**We are relationship owners, not just processors.** Sales agents are transactional \- in and out once. The Service Team owns ongoing client relationships from application through completion.

---

## **1\. WEEKLY COMMUNICATION PROTOCOL**

### **Current State vs. New Requirement**

**CURRENT**: Team does excellent internal Friday updates to each other (see weekly wrap examples) **NEW REQUIREMENT**: Use this same detailed knowledge to communicate directly to clients weekly

### **Standard Communication Requirements**

* **Frequency**: Weekly updates to all active clients (in addition to internal team updates)  
* **Method**: Start with text updates (determine preferred communication method per client)  
* **Tone**: Simple, direct, professional  
* **Source Material**: Use the detailed status information already tracked in Friday internal updates

### **Weekly Update Scripts**

#### **Script A: No Movement Update**

```
Hi [Client Name], this is [Your Name] from RPI's Service Team. 

We did not see any movement on your [case type - annuity/life insurance/etc.] this week. I just wanted to let you know that RPI continues to work on this for you. 

If you have any questions, please don't hesitate to reach out.

Best regards,
[Your Name]
RPI Service Team
```

#### **Script B: Progress Update**

```
Hi [Client Name], this is [Your Name] from RPI's Service Team.

Update on your [case type]: [Brief, specific update about what happened this week]

[If action needed from client]: Your next step is [specific action]. [Timeline if applicable]

[If no action needed]: We'll continue processing and update you next week.

Please reach out if you have any questions.

Best regards,
[Your Name]
RPI Service Team
```

### **Real Examples from Current Internal Updates (Transform to Client Communications):**

**Internal**: "Peggy \- Submitted signed paperwork to Nassau. Communicated to Peggy." **Client Text**: "Hi Peggy, update on your case: We submitted your signed paperwork to Nassau this week. Everything is progressing normally. I'll update you next week on their response."

**Internal**: "Paula Fisette \- emailed part 2 and finance paperwork on the 18th, her EKG/ECG appt is on monday Still in UW with Moo" **Client Text**: "Hi Paula, your EKG appointment is scheduled for Monday. Your case is currently in underwriting with Mutual of Omaha. I'll update you after we hear back from them this week."

**Internal**: "Davis Nassau \- pending funds, they are in route" **Client Text**: "Hi Davis, good news \- your transfer funds are in route to Nassau. Should arrive within the next few business days. I'll confirm once we receive them."

### **Medicare Pipeline**

### **Life Insurance Pipeline**

* **Common Stages**: Application â†’ Medical Requirements â†’ Underwriting â†’ Approval â†’ Policy Issue

## **3\. CLIENT ESCALATION & RECOVERY PROCESS**

### **When Client Escalation Occurs:**

#### **Immediate Response Protocol**

1. **Acknowledge & Apologize** (Team Member)

   * Take immediate accountability  
   * Use de-escalation techniques  
   * Apologize on behalf of company  
2. **Escalate to Nikki** (Within 24 hours)

   * Report the situation  
   * Provide client details and issue summary  
   * Request follow-up call if needed  
3. **Follow-up Actions** (Nikki \+ Team)

   * Personal apology call from Nikki  
   * Handwritten apology note if appropriate  
   * Process review to prevent recurrence

### **Escalation Response Scripts**

#### **Initial Team Member Response**

```
[Client Name], I deeply apologize on behalf of RPI. You're absolutely right - this shouldn't have happened, and we should have made that communication. 

Let me immediately connect you with our Service Team Manager, Nikki Gray, who will personally address this situation and ensure it doesn't happen again.

I'm going to have her reach out to you within [timeframe]. Is [phone number] the best number to reach you?
```

#### **Manager Follow-up Script (Nikki)**

```
Hi [Client Name], this is Nikki Gray, the Service Team Manager at RPI. 

I understand you experienced a communication breakdown with our team, and I want to personally apologize. You needed to hear from me and my staff, and we let you down.

[Acknowledge specific issue]

I take full responsibility for this, and you have my promise that we'll make this right for you and implement changes to prevent this for future clients.

[Discuss resolution steps]

How can I make this right for you today?
```

# Asset Transfer

**Asset Transfer | Default Order of Urgency**

***Aggressively pursue efficiencies** and **reduction in turnaround times\!***

1. Using Firelight, Print just the Transfer/ 1035x Forms to PDF and Save As on your Desktop  
2. Add the Signature Pages from earlier Scan into Signature Page position/ Re-Save  
3. *Use PDF Unlocker App if necessary*  
4. In EngineX- Create Transfer/ 1035x Ticket in Policy/ Edit/ Tabs *(Attach modified 1035x Forms)*  
5. ***When App Status changes to Pending (Carrier assigns Policy \#)- Email forms to NewBiz Rep***  
6. When New Carrier sends 1035x to Old Carrier- Request that they Fax/ E-Mail when possible  
7. When Old Carrier receives New Carrier docs and initiates process  
8. *Is there a way to waive Conservation Period?*  
9. Can it be waived with the Client on the line?  
10. *If they have their proprietary forms that require completion*  
11. Request that they send forms to Client via E-Mail when possible  
12. CCing Producer/ Agency if possible  
13. If they need to mail, request that they use FedEx/ UPS/ USPS Priority for Tracking/ Expediting  
14. Offer to debit your commissions if available  
15. Provide your Account \# for their preferred vendor if not  
16. For Client  
17. Have them sign/ date forms and return via Tracking/ Expedited Method  
18. Produce a Shipping Label for their preferred local vendor (USPS/ UPS/ FedEx)  
19. E-Mail if they have a printer  
20. Ship to them via preferred vendor method, with return label AND envelope enclosed if they don't have a printer  
21. Open a CSR request with details noted/ attached to stay on top of the process  
22. *If they don't require their own forms OR after they receive proprietary forms back from client*  
23. Request that they Wire funds to New Carrier  
24. *L\&A PW Spreadsheet/ Carrier Wire Details Tab for details*  
25. If they won't, request that they use FedEx/ UPS/ USPS Priority for Tracking/ Expediting  
26. Offer to debit your commissions if available  
27. Provide your Account \# for their preferred vendor if not  
28. **Non-Tracked, USPS Regular Mail IS NOT ACCEPTABLE**  
29. [Policy Master Board](https://crm.stackboost.info/secure/Dashboard.jspa?selectPageId=12401)\- Use as Task List for Open Tickets  
30. Monitor Status Daily on New/ Old Carrier Portals- Documenting any updates in Transfer/ 1035x Ticket  
31. Call Old Carrier on the Ticket 2x/ Week until sent to New Carrier  
32. Call New Carrier on the Ticket 2x/ Week until the funds are applied  
33. Close out Transfer/ 1035x Ticket in Policy upon completion

      - [ ] If not, how/ where do we obtain the forms needed to process?

      - [ ] Can you Fax to me with his Authorization?  
            - [ ] If not, who do you use for Express Mail (USPS Priority/ UPS/ FedEx?)  
            - [ ] Can I give you our Account \# to send to him that way?  
      - [ ] Once we get those filled out accordingly, how do we transmit back to you?  
            - [ ] Fax?  What \#?  
            - [ ] E-Mail? What @?  
            - [ ] Portal Upload?  
- [ ] Once you have those, and they're IGO, what's the typical TAT of the Rollover?  
      - [ ] Is this the best \# to call to follow up to make sure you have all you need?  
      - [ ] Is there an e-mail/ contact that would be better?  
- [ ] Is the Rollover check mailed directly to the new IRA Custodian?  
      - [ ] Or sent to Russ, made out to the Custodian, FBO (for the Benefit of) Russ?  
            - [ ] If the latter, who do you use for Express Mail (USPS Priority/ UPS/ FedEx?)  
            - [ ] Can I give you our Account \# to send to him that way?  
- [ ] Thanks for your help, we appreciate you\!\!\!
